## Git Workflow

- Branch from: `main`
- Naming: `feat/<name>`, `fix/<name>`, `chore/<name>`, `deps/<name>`
- Commits: conventional — `feat: add X`, `fix: resolve Y`, `chore: update Z`
- Never push to `main` — open a PR

---

## Boundaries

### ✅ Always do
- Run tests before marking work complete
- Follow the code style rules above
- Write self-documenting code — identifier names over comments

### ⚠️ Ask first (confirm before executing)
- Adding or removing external dependencies
- Changing database schemas or migrations
- Modifying CI/CD pipelines, build config, or infrastructure

### 🚫 Never do
- Commit `.env` files, credentials, or API keys
- Edit `node_modules/` or lock files directly
- Push to `main` — always via PR
- Run destructive operations without explicit user instruction

---

## Testing Conventions

- Unit tests: `<filename>.test.ts` alongside source files
- E2E tests: `tests/e2e/<feature>.spec.ts`
- Tests must pass before a PR can merge

